The real story of Tigoni remains hidden behind these closed gates of private homes and institutions. It is also a story hidden beneath the luscious coffee and tea plantations of Tigoni. A few weeks ago, I took a slow drive around Tigoni in Kiambu just to have a feel of the land which caused a lot of pain in the early years of the Kenya Colony. 

The lush serenity of Tigoni still thrives. The sense of injustice, here, is neatly camouflaged by the well-manicured lawns and where colonial-era bungalows are, occasionally, swallowed up by the hedges and towering trees. 



